                    <!-- Strategy Card 1: Exclusion of Harare -->
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg border-t-4 border-red-500 transition duration-500 hover:shadow-2xl">
                        <div class="text-4xl text-red-500 mb-4">üö´</div>
                        <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Strategic Land Shift</h4>
                        <p class="text-gray-600">Based on financial capacity surveys, the plan to acquire land in **Harare Province has been ruled out**. This decision avoids high costs, congestion, and complex legal dramas associated with urban land.</p>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Strategy Card 2: New Location Focus -->
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg border-t-4 border-oasis-green transition duration-500 hover:shadow-2xl">
                        <div class="text-4xl text-oasis-green mb-4">üìç</div>
                        <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">New Acquisition Focus</h4>
                        <p class="text-gray-600">The current strategy targets acquiring a **privately owned farm** located within a **one-hour radius of Harare**. This strategy ensures affordability, large plot sizes (minimum 1,000 sqm), and clean title deeds.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Plot Size and Quality -->
                <div class="mt-12 text-center max-w-4xl mx-auto p-6 bg-gray-100 rounded-xl shadow-inner">
                    <h4 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2 text-gray-700">Land Size and Architectural Control</h4>
                    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">The majority preference is for plot sizes between **1,000 and 2,000 square meters**. The association will implement a system of **pre-approved architectural plans** to maintain uniformity and quality across the development.</p>
